T1  - 2002 LAWRENCE R. KLEIN LECTURE LIQUIDITY AND ASSET PRICES*
AU  - Kiyotaki, Nobuhiro
AU  - Moore, John
Y1  - 2005/05/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2005.00320.x
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
SP  - 317
EP  - 349
VL  - 46
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2005.00320.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We broadly define liquid assets, or monetary assets, as any asset that can be readily sold in the market and can be held by a number of people in succession before maturity. We ask in what environment is the circulation of liquid assets essential for the smooth running of the economy. By developing a canonical model of a monetary economy (i.e., where the circulation of liquid assets is essential), we are able to examine the interaction between liquidity, asset prices, and aggregate economic activity.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - MONEY AS A MECHANISM IN A BEWLEY ECONOMY*
AU  - Green, Edward J.
AU  - Zhou, Ruilin
Y1  - 2005/05/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/05/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2005.00321.x
T2  - International Economic Review
JF  - International Economic Review
JO  - International Economic Review
SP  - 351
EP  - 371
VL  - 46
IS  - 2
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2005.00321.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We investigate the efficiency property of a monetary economy with spot trade. We prove a conjecture that is essentially due to Bewley (Models of Monetary Economics (1980); Econometrica 51 (1983), 1485?504). The gist is that monetary spot trading is nearly efficient ex ante in an environment where very patient agents can accumulate large enough money stocks to be completely self-insured. We also study examples where a nonmonetary mechanism is preferred ex ante to any monetary mechanism in a stationary environment, and where an inflationary monetary mechanism is preferred ex ante to a laissez-faire or deflationary monetary mechanism in an environment with impatient agents.
ER  - 

