PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-2354.2005.00325.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - A model of fiat money is constructed in which spatial separation and the logistics of communication are made explicit as in search theory, but exchange is organized by profit-seeking business enterprises as in all market economies. Firms mitigate search costs by opening shops that are easily located. Equilibria may exist in which fiat money is used as a universal medium of exchange. When a monetary equilibrium exists, fiat money is essential. The model provides a foundation to cash-in-advance theory, without specifying in advance that one object will be used as the universal medium of exchange.
ER  - 

